      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GOLDEN LODE NZ (7) deserved his brave last-start win in the G3 4YO & 5YO Championship where he had to work racing three wide without cover but toughed it out by 2.8m. Had been terrific against the big guns prior, finishing second in both the Nullarbor and Fremantle Cup. Draws wide but showed last week that he can work and win if need be. Last season's WA Derby winner RUNKLE CRUNCH NZ (8) came from this row and also had to work when sticking on well as runner up to Golden Lode last week. Draws for a trail and is a chance to turn the tables. JUSTCALLMEMIKI NZ (6) drew wider than this when he worked but boxed on to place at Gloucester Park last start. He owns a strong record at this distance. LINCOLN LOU NZ (5) won from the second line two back before a solid second from a similar draw to this in the city last week. Can play a role.",
